Durban - South Africa’s independent schools - and their pupils especially - are celebrating another phenomenal matric year in which 98.76% of candidates passed. 
That’s on par with the previous year. With a 0.09% increase from 2016, the class of 2017 had performed extremely well, said Independent Examinations Board (IEB) chief executive Anne Oberholzer. Of the 11464 full-time and 666 part-time candidates who wrote, 11322 passed. Just 142 pupils failed. For the full story and top achievers get your copy of POST.  POST